abstract: Ms. Yao was a celebrated singer in Shanghai and Hong Kong starting in the 1930s. One of her songs appeared on the soundtrack of the film “Crazy Rich Asians.”
snippet: Ms. Yao was a celebrated singer in Shanghai and Hong Kong starting in the 1930s. One of her songs appeared on the soundtrack of the film “Crazy Rich Asians.”
lead_paragraph: Yao Li, a celebrated singer in Shanghai in the midst of war in the 1930s and ’40s, whose music remained popular after she moved to Hong Kong when China turned communist, died on July 19. She was 96.

abstract: Moscow welcomes the investment from Beijing, but locals say it mostly benefits China, and they bemoan deforestation and the risk of accidents.
snippet: Moscow welcomes the investment from Beijing, but locals say it mostly benefits China, and they bemoan deforestation and the risk of accidents.
lead_paragraph: KANSK, Russia — During the long summer days in Siberia, logging trucks rumble out of the forest heaped with Siberian larch, Scots pine and birch bound for sawmills run by Chinese who can barely believe their good fortune.

abstract: The musical based on the grandiose Meat Loaf album shines a light on its songwriter, Jim Steinman, and the many twists and turns it took to get both projects made.
snippet: The musical based on the grandiose Meat Loaf album shines a light on its songwriter, Jim Steinman, and the many twists and turns it took to get both projects made.
lead_paragraph: In the four decades since it was released, bearing the cover image of a motorcyclist blasting out of a graveyard on his bike, the Meat Loaf album “Bat Out Of Hell” has been described in many ways. Bombastic. Extravagant. Over-the-top.

headline_main: The Robot Apocalypse Has Been Postponed

abstract: The actor and comic has thrived as a professional second banana, even as he endured painful losses in his personal life. A new late-night show could give him a kind of relevance he’s never had before.

lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — “Can I have 45 seconds off before I start the next horrible thing?” David Spade asked.

abstract: Our reporter spent 27 hours as a rider for food-delivery apps. Two-thirds of his customers did not tip.

lead_paragraph: [Update: DoorDash, the nation’s biggest on-demand food delivery app, is changing its tipping model.]
